		<div class="listing-header">
										<h1>Africa-wide S&T organizations</h1>
				 <p>African S&amp;T organizations with operations throughout the continent.</p>
						<br class="cl"/>
		</div> 
		<div id="listing-items">
			
							
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/S-T-organisations/Africa/Africa-wide-S-T-organizations/African-Technology-Policy-Studies-Network-ATPS" title="African Technology Policy Studies Network (ATPS)" alt="link">African Technology Policy Studies Network (ATPS)</a></h2>

	
					<p>ATPS is a multi-disciplinary network of researchers, policy makers and other end-users interested in the generation, promotion and strengthening of innovative technology/industrial policies in Africa. With a regional secretariat in Nairobi, and national chapters in 17 countries, ATPS aims to become a centre of excellence and brokerage between science and technology policy researchers and technology makers and implementers in sub-Saharan Africa. ATPS publishes a series of 'Technopolicy Briefs'.</p>
							<p><span class="date">15/12/2004</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/S-T-organisations/Africa/Africa-wide-S-T-organizations/African-Technology-Policy-Studies-Network-ATPS">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/S-T-organisations/Africa/Africa-wide-S-T-organizations/African-Virtual-University" title="African Virtual University" alt="link">African Virtual University</a></h2>

	
					<p>The AVU is intergovernmental organization created 11 years ago. The AVU has been working since to deliver eLearning contents and to build capacity in francophone, Anglophone and Lusophone Africa. In August 2007, the AVU has revised its mission, vision and strategic objectives as follow:
<b>The Mission</b>&quot;To facilitate the use of effective Open Distance and eLearning (ODeL) Methodologies in African Tertiary Education Institutions&quot;
<b>The Vision</b>&quot;The leading Pan-African Open, Distance and e-Learning (ODeL) network&quot; 
<b>The Strategic Objectives</b>During the period 2007 to 2011, the AVU has identified seven Strategic objectives to be realized through a set of immediate, short-term and medium/long term strategies. These are:


To increase access to higher quality Open Distance and eLearning (ODeL) resources that is relevant to Africa.

To enhance the ODeL capacity of African tertiary educational institutions. 

To enhance and sustain a network of Partner Institutions using ODeL. 

To build and sustain partnerships with institutions that can support the African Virtual University Mission. 

To carry out research and evaluation activities on ODeL on the African Continent. 

To build and sustain a committed and effective African Virtual University organization. 

To develop and implement a fundraising strategy in support of all of the above objectives with focus on Governments, the private sector and International Organizations. 


The AVU has a network of more that 50 partner institutions in 27 African countries. For more information please visit the <a href="http://www.avu.org" target="_blank">AVU website</a> (note that our French and Portuguese website are still under construction).</p>
							<p><span class="date">27/10/2008</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/S-T-organisations/Africa/Africa-wide-S-T-organizations/African-Virtual-University">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="document" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/S-T-organisations/Africa/Africa-wide-S-T-organizations/African-Young-Scientists-Initiative-on-Climate-Change-and-Indigenous-Knowledge-Systems-AYSICCIKS" title="African Young Scientists Initiative on Climate Change and Indigenous Knowledge Systems (AYSICCIKS)" alt="document">African Young Scientists Initiative on Climate Change and Indigenous Knowledge Systems (AYSICCIKS)</a></h2>

	
	
	
	
					<p>The African Young Scientists Initiative on Climate Change and Indigenous Knowledge Systems (AYSICCIKS) held Round Table Discussions on the Role of Young Scientists and Indigenous Knowledge Systems on Climate Change Adaptation and Mitigation at the COP 17 UN Conference on Climate Change. The communiqué can be downloaded below.More information on the AYSICCIKS can be found at <a href="http://aysiccik.blog.com/" target="_blank">http://aysiccik.blog.com/</a>.</p>
							<p><span class="date">12/01/2012</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="document" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/S-T-organisations/Africa/Africa-wide-S-T-organizations/African-Young-Scientists-Initiative-on-Climate-Change-and-Indigenous-Knowledge-Systems-AYSICCIKS">Read more...</a>
